Title: Flexseal DC drain coupling 110mm-125mm
Description: Flexseal DC drain coupling is used to connect, repair and maintain drainage systems and other small diameter non-pressure pipelines. It is available to suit any pipe material up to 275mm outside diameter, drain coupling is designed for use in drainage systems where the resistance to earth loads (usually provided by a standard coupling) is not required. This comprises a moulded EPDM sleeve which is attached using grade 1.4301 (304) worm drive stainless steel clamping bands at either end. Flexseal can also supply the product with nitrile sleeves for use with effluent which may be contaminated with hydrocarbons. Coupling is also available with grade 1.4401 (316) stainless steel for improved corrosion protection.

Title: Flexseal standard couplong 100-115mm
Description: Flexseal standard coupling is specifically designed to connect and repair pipes of different materials or sizes used in sewerage, drainage and other underground applications. When excavation work is required to repair a damaged pipe, Flexseal standard coupling will reduces the amount of time required and minor differences in pipe diameter can be accommodated. The combination of a durable design and excellent sealing properties when tightened to the correct torque enable the Flexseal standard coupling to provide a reliable seal on rough pipe surfaces. It can be combined with Flexseal bushes in order to act as an adaptor between pipelines of differing outside diameters. Standard coupling is made from EN681-1 EPDM rubber and has grade 1.4401 (316) stainless steel clamps and shear bands.

Title: AVK Donkin Series 555 bare shaft gas valve PN16 150mm
Description: Supplied with 150mm flange connections, the AVK Series 555 resilient seat, double-faced gate valve is made of cast iron with a blue transit-coated finish. With a soft seal, internal screw and clear bore, this wedge gate valve is suitable for the isolation of both natural and manufactured gas.  A gate valve, also known as a sluice valve, opens by lifting a barrier out of the path of a fluid. Gate valves normally require minimal space along the pipe axis and offer minimal flow restriction when fully open. A multi-turn valve, operation of a gate valve  is carried out via a threaded stem, turning multiple times to change position.

Title: Flexseal standard coupling 110-121mm
Description: Flexseal standard coupling is specifically designed to connect and repair pipes of different materials or sizes used in sewerage, drainage and other underground applications. When excavation work is required to repair a damaged pipe, Flexseal standard coupling will reduces the amount of time required and minor differences in pipe diameter can be accommodated. The combination of a durable design and excellent sealing properties when tightened to the correct torque enable the Flexseal standard coupling to provide a reliable seal on rough pipe surfaces. It can be combined with Flexseal bushes in order to act as an adaptor between pipelines of differing outside diameters.
